In this article, President Biden expresses his condolences to Queen Elizabeth II on the loss of Prince Philip, highlighting his lifetime of service and contributions. He also discusses his funding priorities for the appropriations process, including two key public health initiatives. The first initiative, called "ARPA-H," aims to develop breakthroughs in detecting, treating, and preventing diseases like Alzheimer's and diabetes, as well as ending cancer. The second initiative proposes a historic funding increase of 50% ($4 billion) to address the ongoing opioid crisis, providing resources for treatment and prevention. Additionally, President Biden emphasizes the importance of investing in Title I schools, VAWA services, and the fight against climate change. He expresses his hope for bipartisan support in Congress for these priorities.